// Trading Economics ì›¹ì‚¬ì´íŠ¸ì—ì„œ ìµœì‹  ë°ì´í„°ë¥¼ ê°€ì ¸ì˜¤ëŠ” Fixed Income ì„œë¹„ìŠ¤
const BASE_URL = 'https://tradingeconomics.com';

// í”„ë¡ì‹œ ì„œë²„ë“¤ì„ ì‚¬ìš©í•œ ì›¹ ìŠ¤í¬ë˜í•‘
const PROXY_SERVICES = [
  'https://api.allorigins.win/raw?url=',
  'https://corsproxy.io/?',
  'https://thingproxy.freeboard.io/fetch/',
  'https://cors.bridged.cc/',
  'https://api.codetabs.com/v1/proxy?quest=',
  'https://cors.eu.org/',
  'https://cors-anywhere.herokuapp.com/',
  'https://corsproxy.io/?',
  'https://api.allorigins.win/raw?url=',
  'https://thingproxy.freeboard.io/fetch/',
  '' // ì§ì ‘ í˜¸ì¶œë„ ì‹œë„
];

// ê³µê°œ APIë¥¼ í†µí•œ ì‹¤ì œ ë°ì´í„° ê°€ì ¸ì˜¤ê¸°
const fetchFromPublicAPI = async () => {
  try {
    console.log('ğŸŒ Trying public API for real data...');
    
    // ë°©ë²• 1: Alpha Vantage API (ë¬´ë£Œ í‹°ì–´)
    try {
      const alphaVantageUrl = 'https://www.alphavantage.co/query?function=TREASURY_YIELD&interval=daily&maturity=10year&apikey=demo';
      
      const response = await fetch(alphaVantageUrl);
      const data = await response.json();
      
      if (data && data.data && data.data.length > 0) {
        const latestYield = parseFloat(data.data[0].value);
        console.log('âœ… Alpha Vantage API successful! US 10Y yield:', latestYield + '%');
        return { us10y: latestYield, source: 'Alpha Vantage' };
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.log('âŒ Alpha Vantage API failed:', error.message);
    }
    
    // ë°©ë²• 2: Yahoo Finance API (ê°„ì ‘ì )
    try {
      const yahooUrl = 'https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v8/finance/chart/%5ETNX?interval=1d&range=1d';
      
      const response = await fetch(yahooUrl);
      const data = await response.json();
      
      if (data && data.chart && data.chart.result && data.chart.result[0]) {
        const result = data.chart.result[0];
        const meta = result.meta;
        const regularMarketPrice = meta.regularMarketPrice;
        
        if (regularMarketPrice) {
          console.log('âœ… Yahoo Finance API successful! US 10Y yield:', regularMarketPrice + '%');
          return { us10y: regularMarketPrice, source: 'Yahoo Finance' };
        }
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.log('âŒ Yahoo Finance API failed:', error.message);
    }
    
    // ë°©ë²• 3: ê°„ë‹¨í•œ JSON API
    try {
      const simpleUrl = 'https://api.jsonbin.io/v3/b/65c8f8c8266cfc3fde8b8c8c';
      
      const response = await fetch(simpleUrl);
      const data = await response.json();
      
      if (data && data.record && data.record.us10y) {
        const us10y = data.record.us10y;
        console.log('âœ… Simple API successful! US 10Y yield:', us10y + '%');
        return { us10y: us10y, source: 'Simple API' };
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.log('âŒ Simple API failed:', error.message);
    }
    
    throw new Error('All public APIs failed');
  } catch (error) {
    console.log('âŒ All public APIs failed:', error.message);
    return null;
  }
};

// í”„ë¡ì‹œë¥¼ ì‚¬ìš©í•œ ì›¹ ìŠ¤í¬ë˜í•‘
const fetchWithProxy = async (url, proxyIndex = 0) => {
  if (proxyIndex >= PROXY_SERVICES.length) {
    throw new Error('All proxy attempts failed');
  }

  try {
    const proxyUrl = PROXY_SERVICES[proxyIndex] + url;
    console.log(`ğŸ”— Trying proxy ${proxyIndex + 1}/${PROXY_SERVICES.length}: ${proxyUrl.substring(0, 50)}...`);
    
    const response = await fetch(proxyUrl, {
      method: 'GET',
      headers: {
        'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8',
        'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36',
        'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.9',
        'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br',
        'Connection': 'keep-alive',
        'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1'
      },
      timeout: 10000 // 10ì´ˆ íƒ€ì„ì•„ì›ƒ
    });

    if (!response.ok) {
      throw new Error(`HTTP error! status: ${response.status}`);
    }

    const html = await response.text();
    
    if (html.length < 1000) {
      throw new Error('Response too short, likely an error page');
    }
    
    console.log(`âœ… Proxy ${proxyIndex + 1} successful! HTML length: ${html.length} characters`);
    return html;
  } catch (error) {
    console.log(`âŒ Proxy ${proxyIndex + 1} failed: ${error.message}`);
    return fetchWithProxy(url, proxyIndex + 1);
  }
};

// HTMLì—ì„œ ê¸ˆë¦¬ ë°ì´í„° ì¶”ì¶œ (Trading Economics Calendar í…Œì´ë¸”ì—ì„œ ì¶”ì¶œ)
const extractInterestRateFromHTML = (html, country) => {
  try {
    // Trading Economics Calendar í…Œì´ë¸”ì—ì„œ ê°€ì¥ ìµœì‹ ì˜ ì‹¤ì œ ë°ì´í„° TEForcast ê°’ ì¶”ì¶œ
    
    // í…Œì´ë¸” íŒ¨í„´ ì°¾ê¸° (Calendar, GMTê°€ í¬í•¨ëœ í…Œì´ë¸”)
    const tablePattern = /<table[^>]*>.*?Calendar.*?GMT.*?<\/table>/is;
    const tableMatch = html.match(tablePattern);
    
    if (!tableMatch) {
      console.log(`No calendar table found for ${country}`);
      return null;
    }
    
    const tableHTML = tableMatch[0];
    
    // í…Œì´ë¸” í–‰ë“¤ ì¶”ì¶œ
    const rowPattern = /<tr[^>]*>.*?<\/tr>/gis;
    const rows = tableHTML.match(rowPattern);
    
    if (!rows || rows.length < 2) {
      console.log(`No rows found in calendar table for ${country}`);
      return null;
    }
    
    // í˜„ì¬ ë‚ ì§œ ê°€ì ¸ì˜¤ê¸°
    const currentDate = new Date();
    const currentDateString = currentDate.toISOString().split('T')[0]; // YYYY-MM-DD í˜•ì‹
    
    console.log(`Current date: ${currentDateString}`);
    
    // ì²« ë²ˆì§¸ í–‰ì€ í—¤ë”ì´ë¯€ë¡œ ì œì™¸í•˜ê³ , ë‘ ë²ˆì§¸ í–‰ë¶€í„° ê²€ìƒ‰
    // ê°€ì¥ ìµœì‹ ì˜ ì‹¤ì œ ë°ì´í„°(Actual ê°’ì´ ìˆëŠ” í–‰)ì˜ TEForcast ê°’ ì°¾ê¸°
    let latestRate = null;
    let latestDate = null;
    
    for (let i = 1; i < rows.length; i++) {
      const row = rows[i];
      
      // TD íƒœê·¸ë“¤ ì¶”ì¶œ
      const tdPattern = /<td[^>]*>(.*?)<\/td>/gis;
      const tds = row.match(tdPattern);
      
      if (tds && tds.length >= 7) { // Calendar, GMT, Reference, Actual, Previous, Consensus, TEForecast
        // ì²« ë²ˆì§¸ TD: ë‚ ì§œ
        const dateTD = tds[0];
        // ë„¤ ë²ˆì§¸ TD: Actual ê°’
        const actualTD = tds[3];
        // ì¼ê³± ë²ˆì§¸ TD: TEForcast ê°’
        const teForcastTD = tds[6];
        
        // ë‚ ì§œ ì¶”ì¶œ (YYYY-MM-DD í˜•ì‹)
        const datePattern = /(\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2})/;
        const dateMatch = dateTD.match(datePattern);
        
        if (dateMatch) {
          const date = dateMatch[1];
          
          // ë‚ ì§œê°€ í˜„ì¬ ë‚ ì§œë³´ë‹¤ ë¯¸ë˜ì¸ì§€ í™•ì¸
          if (date > currentDateString) {
            console.log(`Skipping future date: ${date}`);
            continue; // ë¯¸ë˜ ë‚ ì§œëŠ” ê±´ë„ˆë›°ê¸°
          }
          
          // Actual ê°’ì´ ìˆëŠ”ì§€ í™•ì¸ (ë¹ˆ ê°’ì´ ì•„ë‹Œì§€)
          const actualPattern = /(\d+\.\d+)/;
          const actualMatch = actualTD.match(actualPattern);
          
          if (actualMatch) {
            // Actual ê°’ì´ ìˆìœ¼ë©´ ì‹¤ì œ ë°ì´í„°ë¡œ ê°„ì£¼
            const teForcastPattern = /(\d+\.\d+)/;
            const teForcastMatch = teForcastTD.match(teForcastPattern);
            
            if (teForcastMatch) {
              const rate = parseFloat(teForcastMatch[1]);
              
              // ë” ìµœì‹  ë‚ ì§œì¸ì§€ í™•ì¸
              if (!latestDate || date > latestDate) {
                latestDate = date;
                latestRate = rate;
                console.log(`Found actual data: ${rate}% for date: ${date}`);
              }
            }
          } else {
            console.log(`No actual data for date: ${date}, skipping`);
          }
        }
      }
    }
    
    if (latestRate) {
      console.log(`Found latest actual rate for ${country}: ${latestRate}% (Date: ${latestDate})`);
      return latestRate;
    }
    
    // ì‹¤ì œ ë°ì´í„°ë¥¼ ì°¾ì§€ ëª»í•œ ê²½ìš°, ëª¨ë“  TDì—ì„œ ìˆ«ì ì°¾ê¸° (ë¯¸ë˜ ì œì™¸)
    console.log(`No actual data found for ${country}, searching all TDs (excluding future dates)...`);
    
    for (let i = 1; i < rows.length; i++) {
      const row = rows[i];
      
      // ë‚ ì§œ ì¶”ì¶œ (YYYY-MM-DD í˜•ì‹)
      const datePattern = /(\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2})/;
      const dateMatch = row.match(datePattern);
      
      if (dateMatch) {
        const date = dateMatch[1];
        
        // ë‚ ì§œê°€ í˜„ì¬ ë‚ ì§œë³´ë‹¤ ë¯¸ë˜ì¸ì§€ í™•ì¸
        if (date > currentDateString) {
          continue; // ë¯¸ë˜ ë‚ ì§œëŠ” ê±´ë„ˆë›°ê¸°
        }
        
        // ëª¨ë“  ìˆ«ì.ìˆ«ì íŒ¨í„´ ì°¾ê¸°
        const numberPattern = /(\d+\.\d+)/g;
        const numberMatches = row.match(numberPattern);
        
        if (numberMatches && numberMatches.length > 0) {
          // ê°€ì¥ í° ê°’ì´ ë³´í†µ ë©”ì¸ ê¸ˆë¦¬
          const rates = numberMatches.map(match => parseFloat(match));
          const maxRate = Math.max(...rates);
          
          // ë” ìµœì‹  ë‚ ì§œì¸ì§€ í™•ì¸
          if (!latestDate || date > latestDate) {
            latestDate = date;
            latestRate = maxRate;
          }
        }
      }
    }
    
    if (latestRate) {
      console.log(`Found latest rate from all TDs for ${country}: ${latestRate}% (Date: ${latestDate})`);
      return latestRate;
    }
    
    // í…Œì´ë¸”ì—ì„œ ì°¾ì§€ ëª»í•œ ê²½ìš°, ê¸°ì¡´ íŒ¨í„´ìœ¼ë¡œ ë°±ì—… ì‹œë„
    console.log(`No rate found in table for ${country}, trying backup patterns...`);
    
    // ë°±ì—…: ì²« ë²ˆì§¸ ë¬¸ì¥ì—ì„œ ê¸ˆë¦¬ ì¶”ì¶œ
    const firstSentenceMatch = html.match(/<p[^>]*>([^<]+)<\/p>/i) || 
                              html.match(/<div[^>]*>([^<]+)<\/div>/i) ||
                              html.match(/<span[^>]*>([^<]+)<\/span>/i);
    
    const textToSearch = firstSentenceMatch ? firstSentenceMatch[1] : html;
    
    const patterns = [
      /(\d+\.\d+)%/g,
      /yield.*?(\d+\.\d+)%/i,
      /(\d+\.\d+)%.*?yield/i,
      /bond.*?(\d+\.\d+)%/i,
      /(\d+\.\d+)%.*?bond/i
    ];
    
    for (const pattern of patterns) {
      const matches = textToSearch.match(pattern);
      if (matches && matches.length > 0) {
        const rates = matches.map(match => {
          const rateMatch = match.match(/(\d+\.\d+)%/);
          return rateMatch ? parseFloat(rateMatch[1]) : 0;
        });
        
        const maxRate = Math.max(...rates);
        if (maxRate > 0) {
          console.log(`Found rate from backup pattern for ${country}: ${maxRate}%`);
          return maxRate;
        }
      }
    }
    
    console.log(`No rate found for ${country}`);
    return null;
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error extracting data from HTML:', error);
    return null;
  }
};

